Migrating to the cloud using Virtual Machines is often the easiest approach, known as “lift-and-shift”.

Existing on-premise applications can be moved to Azure VMs without major changes.

For example, a company running a legacy application on physical servers can migrate it directly to a VM in Azure.

A real-life use case is enterprises modernizing infrastructure without rewriting applications.

Another example is quick migration during data center shutdowns.

Tools like Azure Migrate help assess and move workloads efficiently.

This approach reduces migration complexity and accelerates cloud adoption.
